#trend - long term increase or decrease in the data.does not have to be linear - can be change in direction
#seasonal - when ts affected by seasonal factors, time of year or day of week - ALWAYS of a fixed and known period
#cyclic - a cycle occurs when the data exhibit rises and falls that ARE NOT of a fixed frequency - usually due to economic conditions - related to biz cycle - duration of fluctuations is at least 2 yrs
# do not confuse cyclic with seasonal!!!
#RANDOM - no trend, no seasonality, no cyclic behavior - no strong pattern to help develop a forecasting model